panPage(25.10)                                                  panPage(25.10)

Name
       panPage - Pans the viewable window in pages defined by the offsets

Syntax
       panPage

       [-help]

       <x><y>

       Pans  the  viewable window in pages defined by the offsets. The size of
       each page is equal to the size of the current viewable window. Use this
       command at any stage of the design flow.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each panPage parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man panPage.

       <x y>  Specifies xand y offsets to indicate number of pages to  pan.  A
              positive value of <x> specifies a pan of <x> pages to the right.
              A positive number of <y> specifies a pan of <y> pages toward the
              top.

              You can specify integer values for <x> and <y>.

Examples
              * The  following  command  pans  the display to the right by one
                page

                panPage 1 0

              * The following command pans the display to the left by one page

                panPage -1 0

